## Structure

```
app/
  [[...slug]]/route.ts   # catch-all: serves captured pages
  api/                   # generated API route stubs
captured-pages/          # rendered HTML snapshots
fixtures/                # captured API response fixtures
public/_assets/          # downloaded static assets
prisma/schema.prisma     # generated DB schema (SQLite)
route-map.json           # pathname → HTML file mapping
```

## Wiring up real logic

Each file in `app/api/` returns a fixture by default. Replace the body with
real database calls, external API calls, etc. The Prisma models and
`.env.example` give you a starting point for persistence.
